# Request temporary access

This topic describes how to make a one-time request for access to a web
app that isn\'t in the User portal, or for elevated permissions to an
available web app.

::: {.important madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.not-free-trial"}
:::

## Overview

policies determine what web apps are available in the User portal, along
with the level of privileges you have within those web apps. If you need
to access a web app that doesn\'t appear in your User portal or if you
need additional permissions on an available web app to perform a task,
you can make a one-time request for temporary access.

## Request temporary access to a web app

### Prerequiste {#prerequiste .step madcap:autonum="Step 1: "}

### Sign in to the User portal {#sign-in-to-the-user-portal .step madcap:autonum="Step 2: "}

Sign in to , and go to the [Applications]{.Emphasis} page.

### Create the request {#create-the-request .step madcap:autonum="Step 3: "}

1.  If you don\'t see the web app you need in the User portal, do the
    following:

    1.  Click [Add Apps]{.Emphasis}.

    2.  In the App Catalog, click the [DevOps ]{.Emphasis}category and
        search for the web app you need.

        ::: note
        Search by web app name, not by cloud provider.
        :::

    3.  Next to the relevant web app, click [Request]{.Emphasis}.

2.  If you see the web app you need in the User portal, click it.

3.  If you don\'t see the role, permission set, or scope that you need
    in the list, click [Request access]{.Emphasis}.

### Provide the web app and request details {#provide-the-web-app-and-request-details .step madcap:autonum="Step 4: "}

